On December 14, 2018, the President signed into law several bills that designate various facilities of the United States Postal Service and the Department of Veterans Affairs. These include naming the Department of Veterans Affairs community-based outpatient clinic in Statesboro, Georgia as the 'Ray Hendrix Veterans Clinic', designating the facility of the United States Postal Service located at 3s101 Rockwell Street in Warrenville, Illinois as the "Corporal Jeffery Allen Williams Post Office Building", designating the facility of the United States Postal Service located at 1234 Saint Johns Place in Brooklyn, New York as the "Major Robert Odell Owens Post Office", designating the facility of the United States Postal Service located at 413 Washington Avenue in Belleville, New Jersey as the "Private Henry Svehla Post Office Building", and designating the facility of the United States Postal Service located at 120 12th Street Lobby in Columbus, Georgia as the "Richard W. Williams, Jr., Chapter of the Triple Nickles (555th P.I.A.) Post Office".